WEBVTT

1
00:00:01.506 --> 00:00:04.467
[eerie music]

2
00:00:04.551 --> 00:00:10.473
<i>♪♪</i>

3
00:00:10.557 --> 00:00:12.308
[man 1] Arizona license.

4
00:00:12.392 --> 00:00:14.477
Joseph "Lee-forn."

5
00:00:14.561 --> 00:00:18.189
[man 2] Probably fake.

6
00:00:18.273 --> 00:00:22.360
[man 1] Hey. He's up.

7
00:00:22.444 --> 00:00:24.279
- [Joe groans]
- Oh.

8
00:00:24.362 --> 00:00:27.198
Shit.

9
00:00:27.282 --> 00:00:28.408
What are you doing all the way

10
00:00:28.491 --> 00:00:32.829
out in LA. Mr. "Lee-forn"?

11
00:00:32.912 --> 00:00:35.331
[grunts] Sightseeing.

12
00:00:35.415 --> 00:00:37.709
[chuckles] He's a funny guy.

13
00:00:37.792 --> 00:00:38.918
Did you think he'd be a funny guy?

14
00:00:39.002 --> 00:00:40.336
Doesn't look too funny.

15
00:00:40.420 --> 00:00:41.337
[grunts]

16
00:00:41.421 --> 00:00:43.631
[coughing]

17
00:00:47.802 --> 00:00:49.429
What are you doing here?

18
00:00:49.512 --> 00:00:51.222
[groans]

19
00:00:54.601 --> 00:00:55.977
[breathing raggedly]

20
00:00:56.061 --> 00:00:59.314
Looking for my niece and nephew--

21
00:00:59.397 --> 00:01:01.858
Billie Tsosie and Leroy Gorman.

22
00:01:06.780 --> 00:01:08.782
This them?

23
00:01:08.865 --> 00:01:10.784
The girl's Billie.

24
00:01:10.867 --> 00:01:14.204
Man's her grandpa.

25
00:01:14.287 --> 00:01:16.998
And you were looking
for them at a McNair party

26
00:01:17.082 --> 00:01:18.875
with a gun?

27
00:01:18.958 --> 00:01:21.169
Who?

28
00:01:21.252 --> 00:01:23.379
Beno put you up to this?

29
00:01:23.463 --> 00:01:25.840
I don't know any Beno.

30
00:01:25.924 --> 00:01:28.635
Just looking for Billie.

31
00:01:28.718 --> 00:01:31.721
She's a 16-year-old girl.
and she's a runaway.

32
00:01:31.805 --> 00:01:33.097
She was at that party.

33
00:01:33.181 --> 00:01:39.687
<i>♪♪</i>

34
00:01:39.771 --> 00:01:41.231
[grunts]

35
00:01:51.908 --> 00:01:55.787
If you knew she was inside
and you were looking for her.

36
00:01:55.870 --> 00:01:57.914
what were you doing
across the street?

37
00:02:01.126 --> 00:02:03.044
Yeah.

38
00:02:03.128 --> 00:02:06.381
[grunts] Son of a bitch!

39
00:02:06.464 --> 00:02:09.134
Okay. I'm a cop.

40
00:02:09.217 --> 00:02:11.427
I'm a cop.

41
00:02:11.511 --> 00:02:16.349
Lieutenant Leaphorn.
Navajo Tribal Police.

42
00:02:16.432 --> 00:02:19.644
Have somebody from your
field office call the BIA.

43
00:02:19.727 --> 00:02:21.604
They'll confirm it.

44
00:02:21.688 --> 00:02:24.023
<i>♪♪</i>

45
00:02:24.107 --> 00:02:26.609
Look… [sighs]

46
00:02:26.693 --> 00:02:28.778
There were two murders
on the reservation.

47
00:02:28.862 --> 00:02:31.781
Witness ran out here-- Billie.

48
00:02:31.865 --> 00:02:34.450
That's who we're trying to find.

49
00:02:34.534 --> 00:02:37.078
Maybe you're looking
for her. too. huh?

50
00:02:37.162 --> 00:02:40.456
Is that why you had
a camera set up?

51
00:02:40.540 --> 00:02:42.167
Maybe we can help each other.

52
00:02:42.250 --> 00:02:47.964
<i>♪♪</i>

53
00:02:48.047 --> 00:02:49.799
If you really want to help.

54
00:02:49.883 --> 00:02:51.175
you'll go back to Arizona

55
00:02:51.259 --> 00:02:53.052
before someone puts you in the ground.

56
00:02:53.136 --> 00:02:57.140
<i>♪♪</i>

57
00:02:57.223 --> 00:02:59.142
[grunts]

58
00:03:05.231 --> 00:03:07.817
Son of a bitch.

59
00:03:07.901 --> 00:03:14.782
<i>♪♪</i>

60
00:03:25.543 --> 00:03:28.421
[moody guitar music]

61
00:03:28.504 --> 00:03:35.428
{\an8}<i>♪♪</i>

62
00:03:47.982 --> 00:03:49.901
{\an8}[car horns blare]

63
00:03:59.202 --> 00:04:01.204
{\an8}[flames crackling]

64
00:04:01.287 --> 00:04:07.210
{\an8}<i>♪♪</i>

65
00:04:17.345 --> 00:04:20.223
[soft dramatic music]

66
00:04:20.306 --> 00:04:27.188
<i>♪♪</i>

67
00:04:28.314 --> 00:04:29.983
[phone rings]

68
00:04:33.444 --> 00:04:34.779
Joe?

69
00:04:51.546 --> 00:04:53.131
Hi.

70
00:04:55.633 --> 00:04:57.552
I. um…

71
00:05:09.897 --> 00:05:12.400
[groans softly]

72
00:05:12.483 --> 00:05:14.235
I'll get you in for an X-ray.

73
00:05:14.319 --> 00:05:16.321
No. just-- I'll take some ice.

74
00:05:16.404 --> 00:05:17.488
I got to get back.

75
00:05:22.285 --> 00:05:24.203
Hold it.

76
00:05:32.503 --> 00:05:37.091
- [Joe groans]
- [chuckles] I moved 600 miles away.

77
00:05:37.175 --> 00:05:40.344
and I'm still patching you up.

78
00:05:40.428 --> 00:05:43.347
It's not like I knew you'd be here.

79
00:05:43.431 --> 00:05:44.849
Come on. Joe.

80
00:05:44.932 --> 00:05:47.727
There are four other
hospitals within ten miles.

81
00:05:47.852 --> 00:05:51.355
{\an8}Well. none of those
would take my CIB.

82
00:05:54.150 --> 00:05:57.403
{\an8}Leave that on until it's warm.

83
00:05:57.487 --> 00:06:00.740
{\an8}And get more ice. Wrap it.

84
00:06:00.823 --> 00:06:03.242
{\an8}Then come back for an X-ray.

85
00:06:10.583 --> 00:06:13.002
Are you happy here?

86
00:06:21.344 --> 00:06:23.179
I like the city.

87
00:06:23.262 --> 00:06:24.972
I like this hospital.

88
00:06:25.139 --> 00:06:28.267
I like knowing what I do
makes a difference.

89
00:06:28.351 --> 00:06:29.977
that when people
are hurt and scared.

90
00:06:30.061 --> 00:06:32.230
they can come here and feel safe.

91
00:06:32.313 --> 00:06:36.150
And I like. for the first time in 30 years.

92
00:06:36.234 --> 00:06:38.152
I'm not making myself sick with worry

93
00:06:38.236 --> 00:06:40.279
because you're too
stubborn to get an X-ray.

94
00:06:40.363 --> 00:06:46.828
<i>♪♪</i>

95
00:06:46.911 --> 00:06:48.663
Okay.

96
00:06:48.746 --> 00:06:50.623
I'll get the X-ray.

97
00:06:53.251 --> 00:06:55.253
I just need to let Chee
and Bern know where I'm at.

98
00:06:55.336 --> 00:06:56.838
All right?

99
00:06:56.921 --> 00:06:58.673
You can use the
phone at the nurse's station.

100
00:06:58.756 --> 00:07:01.467
then go to the waiting room.

101
00:07:01.551 --> 00:07:04.345
They'll find you when they're ready.

102
00:07:08.516 --> 00:07:10.017
[door clicks]

103
00:07:11.477 --> 00:07:12.395
[door thuds]

104
00:07:19.861 --> 00:07:23.197
[phone rings]

105
00:07:23.281 --> 00:07:26.617
[soft dramatic music]

106
00:07:26.701 --> 00:07:28.619
Hey.

107
00:07:28.703 --> 00:07:30.621
You sure you don't
want to see a doctor?

108
00:07:30.705 --> 00:07:32.457
Oh. I'm fine.

109
00:07:32.540 --> 00:07:34.208
Sonny gave me some pills.

110
00:07:34.292 --> 00:07:36.169
They're wearing off.

111
00:07:42.216 --> 00:07:44.177
Are we gonna get past this?

112
00:07:48.723 --> 00:07:50.224
I don't know.

113
00:07:54.437 --> 00:07:57.106
Do you want to?

114
00:07:57.190 --> 00:07:58.691
[door clicks]

115
00:07:58.774 --> 00:08:00.485
He's done.

116
00:08:07.283 --> 00:08:09.785
What'd they say?

117
00:08:09.869 --> 00:08:14.123
Ah. just a bump on the head.
bruised ribs.

118
00:08:14.207 --> 00:08:15.666
I'll be all right.

119
00:08:15.750 --> 00:08:18.920
What happened?

120
00:08:19.003 --> 00:08:20.630
Someone else
was watching that party.

121
00:08:20.713 --> 00:08:23.925
I went to check it out. got jumped.

122
00:08:24.008 --> 00:08:26.511
Sons of bitches got my gun.

123
00:08:26.594 --> 00:08:27.929
Sonny's guys?

124
00:08:28.012 --> 00:08:32.016
No. they're white guys. late thirties.

125
00:08:32.099 --> 00:08:34.560
One was wiry. had a big mustache.

126
00:08:34.644 --> 00:08:38.064
The other one was bigger.
He had a little baby face.

127
00:08:40.316 --> 00:08:42.276
You know. I think they might
have been old friends of yours.

128
00:08:44.695 --> 00:08:45.988
FBI?

129
00:08:46.072 --> 00:08:50.409
Yeah. they called it "McNair party."

130
00:08:50.493 --> 00:08:53.746
That mean anything to you?

131
00:08:53.829 --> 00:08:55.957
Mustache guy.

132
00:08:56.040 --> 00:08:58.209
Was he popping antacids?

133
00:08:58.292 --> 00:09:01.420
[dramatic music]

134
00:09:15.685 --> 00:09:17.019
Here you go.

135
00:09:19.021 --> 00:09:20.940
[car horn honks]

136
00:09:25.069 --> 00:09:27.947
[sirens blaring distantly]

137
00:09:30.783 --> 00:09:32.368
Here.

138
00:09:34.704 --> 00:09:37.623
- You hear from Leroy?
- No.

139
00:09:41.294 --> 00:09:44.589
Sure he's in LA?

140
00:09:44.672 --> 00:09:46.716
There's some rez cops looking for him.

141
00:09:46.799 --> 00:09:50.094
They think he is.

142
00:09:50.177 --> 00:09:51.762
Hm.

143
00:09:54.223 --> 00:09:59.270
Me and Leroy got in a
fight a week and a half ago.

144
00:09:59.353 --> 00:10:01.439
Something stupid.

145
00:10:01.522 --> 00:10:05.026
I don't know. I thought he'd
be back in a couple of days.

146
00:10:05.109 --> 00:10:07.820
He does that sometimes.

147
00:10:07.903 --> 00:10:11.282
But then. I don't know.

148
00:10:11.365 --> 00:10:13.492
He usually calls.

149
00:10:13.576 --> 00:10:16.412
[soft dramatic music]

150
00:10:16.495 --> 00:10:19.999
<i>♪♪</i>

151
00:10:20.082 --> 00:10:22.752
Can I ask you something?

152
00:10:22.835 --> 00:10:26.756
You said those guys are criminals.

153
00:10:26.839 --> 00:10:30.468
What do they do?

154
00:10:30.551 --> 00:10:34.847
We just got to find Leroy
before the German lady does.

155
00:10:34.930 --> 00:10:36.807
Do you have any family?

156
00:10:36.891 --> 00:10:43.814
<i>♪♪</i>

157
00:10:47.902 --> 00:10:49.570
My grandpa's dead.

158
00:10:49.654 --> 00:10:52.698
I never knew my dad.

159
00:10:52.782 --> 00:10:55.326
And my mom. she--

160
00:10:55.409 --> 00:10:58.037
she died right after I was born. so…

161
00:11:00.414 --> 00:11:02.625
Leroy's the only family I got left.

162
00:11:02.708 --> 00:11:07.046
<i>♪♪</i>

163
00:11:09.256 --> 00:11:10.966
[elevator dings]

164
00:11:11.050 --> 00:11:12.301
These people. they don't care about us.

165
00:11:12.385 --> 00:11:14.804
They don't care about what we're doing.

166
00:11:14.887 --> 00:11:17.056
And they won't lift a
finger to help local cops.

167
00:11:17.139 --> 00:11:18.849
especially Indian ones.

168
00:11:18.933 --> 00:11:20.684
What we have to do

169
00:11:20.768 --> 00:11:24.647
is make it seem
like we're helping them.

170
00:11:24.730 --> 00:11:27.066
- Cheeseburger!
- Shaw.

171
00:11:27.149 --> 00:11:29.735
As I live and breathe.

172
00:11:29.819 --> 00:11:31.570
- Hey. man.
- No. no. no.

173
00:11:31.654 --> 00:11:34.365
[both grunt]

174
00:11:34.448 --> 00:11:36.742
Last I heard. you were
working some undercover thing.

175
00:11:36.826 --> 00:11:39.120
Yeah. I was. but now
I'm just a lowly beat cop

176
00:11:39.203 --> 00:11:41.414
at the Navajo Tribal Police.

177
00:11:41.497 --> 00:11:43.040
This is Lieutenant Joe Leaphorn

178
00:11:43.124 --> 00:11:44.917
and Sergeant Bernadette Mañuelito.

179
00:11:45.000 --> 00:11:47.503
We. uh. met.

180
00:11:47.586 --> 00:11:49.213
How you doing. asshole?

181
00:11:49.296 --> 00:11:51.799
I called the BIA.
Sorry about the mix-up.

182
00:11:51.882 --> 00:11:55.386
Big cases put everyone on edge.
and this one's big.

183
00:11:55.469 --> 00:11:57.596
Understood.

184
00:11:57.680 --> 00:12:02.101
What's a few cracked
ribs between friends. huh?

185
00:12:02.184 --> 00:12:05.062
[quirky dramatic music]

186
00:12:05.146 --> 00:12:08.232
<i>♪♪</i>

187
00:12:08.315 --> 00:12:09.900
Had to take the ammo.

188
00:12:09.984 --> 00:12:13.154
Sorry about that.

189
00:12:13.237 --> 00:12:16.699
This is my colleague. Frank Welles.

190
00:12:16.782 --> 00:12:18.826
We're happy to chat as a favor to Chee.

191
00:12:18.909 --> 00:12:20.870
but you understand there's
only so much we can share.

192
00:12:20.953 --> 00:12:22.788
Course.

193
00:12:22.872 --> 00:12:25.708
You've been following the
McNair business in the news?

194
00:12:25.791 --> 00:12:29.545
Never heard the name
until our private van tour.

195
00:12:29.628 --> 00:12:33.048
All right. well. he owns
an import/export business.

196
00:12:33.132 --> 00:12:35.509
McNair Factoring. down in San Pedro.

197
00:12:35.593 --> 00:12:37.052
We got a tip last year that he had

198
00:12:37.136 --> 00:12:40.014
his hands in a few
less-than-legal cookie jars.

199
00:12:40.097 --> 00:12:42.892
Two months ago. we finally
got enough to make the arrest.

200
00:12:42.975 --> 00:12:44.602
Now he's in Men's Central awaiting trial.

201
00:12:44.685 --> 00:12:45.769
but the U.S. attorney's

202
00:12:45.853 --> 00:12:47.438
starting to think he might walk.

203
00:12:47.521 --> 00:12:49.148
You can't make the case?

204
00:12:49.231 --> 00:12:52.067
Key part of our case
is based on witness testimony.

205
00:12:52.151 --> 00:12:55.613
and a couple witnesses disappeared.

206
00:12:55.696 --> 00:12:58.407
And then the rest realized
they don't remember anything.

207
00:12:58.491 --> 00:12:59.783
[inhales sharply]

208
00:12:59.867 --> 00:13:01.577
Was Albert Gorman
one of those witnesses?

209
00:13:01.660 --> 00:13:04.872
We can't give you that information.

210
00:13:04.955 --> 00:13:06.957
Well. if he was. he's dead.

211
00:13:10.002 --> 00:13:11.670
Hm.

212
00:13:11.754 --> 00:13:14.757
He was murdered three days
ago on the Navajo reservation.

213
00:13:14.840 --> 00:13:18.302
Killer's a German woman.
5'9". blonde. 40s.

214
00:13:18.385 --> 00:13:20.846
Drives a green Dodge van.

215
00:13:20.930 --> 00:13:24.433
See. the girl we're looking for
is a witness to the murder.

216
00:13:24.517 --> 00:13:26.936
We find her.
maybe she can give you

217
00:13:27.019 --> 00:13:29.813
something else to hang on McNair.

218
00:13:29.897 --> 00:13:31.815
Come on. man.
We're on the same team.

219
00:13:31.899 --> 00:13:34.652
Our girl is clearly
caught up in all this.

220
00:13:34.735 --> 00:13:37.154
The sooner we find her.
the better it is for all of us.

221
00:13:37.238 --> 00:13:39.448
This whole thing's
hanging by a thread.

222
00:13:39.532 --> 00:13:41.283
Okay. everything's locked down.

223
00:13:41.367 --> 00:13:44.161
I can't spare resources
chasing a 16-year-old runaway

224
00:13:44.245 --> 00:13:47.331
on a tribal cop's say-so--
even a friend's.

225
00:13:47.414 --> 00:13:49.500
Let us look at what you have--

226
00:13:49.583 --> 00:13:52.378
surveillance photos.
known associates.

227
00:13:52.461 --> 00:13:53.879
addresses. phone numbers.

228
00:13:53.963 --> 00:13:55.130
And we could do the rest if you--

229
00:13:55.214 --> 00:13:58.008
No.

230
00:13:58.092 --> 00:14:00.344
She's going to die if we don't find her.

231
00:14:00.427 --> 00:14:02.471
[tense music]

232
00:14:02.555 --> 00:14:05.516
You get that. right?

233
00:14:05.599 --> 00:14:09.019
<i>♪♪</i>

234
00:14:09.103 --> 00:14:12.106
I'm sorry.

235
00:14:12.189 --> 00:14:13.315
[elevator dings]

236
00:14:13.399 --> 00:14:14.733
Excuse me.

237
00:14:19.405 --> 00:14:21.824
Spent two years listening to stories

238
00:14:21.907 --> 00:14:24.743
about that asshole's
bowling league-- two years.

239
00:14:24.827 --> 00:14:26.537
And he can't even just
give us a little information?

240
00:14:26.620 --> 00:14:28.581
Hey. Chee. we knew it was a long shot.

241
00:14:32.209 --> 00:14:34.169
I shouldn't have come back here.

242
00:14:34.253 --> 00:14:36.046
[lid squeaks]

243
00:14:38.132 --> 00:14:40.217
[inhales sharply]

244
00:14:40.301 --> 00:14:41.635
[sighs]

245
00:14:41.719 --> 00:14:44.263
Look. our situation hasn't changed.

246
00:14:44.346 --> 00:14:45.764
Billie's still looking for Leroy.

247
00:14:45.848 --> 00:14:47.558
We find him. we can still find her.

248
00:14:47.641 --> 00:14:50.394
Except we haven't
been able to find her.

249
00:14:50.477 --> 00:14:52.396
No. we haven't.

250
00:14:54.356 --> 00:14:56.817
But maybe Mike Garcia can.

251
00:15:02.781 --> 00:15:05.701
[groovy upbeat music]

252
00:15:05.784 --> 00:15:12.708
<i>♪♪</i>

253
00:15:15.044 --> 00:15:17.254
Hey. man. You guys buying?

254
00:15:17.338 --> 00:15:18.839
What you got?

255
00:15:21.634 --> 00:15:23.594
Nah. man. not this crap.

256
00:15:23.677 --> 00:15:25.012
I'll sell for half of what it's worth.

257
00:15:25.095 --> 00:15:26.138
I just need the money quick.

258
00:15:26.221 --> 00:15:29.308
Ain't even worth half.

259
00:15:29.391 --> 00:15:31.685
[loudly] Come on. man.
I just need the money. please.

260
00:15:31.769 --> 00:15:33.646
Look. man. I told you we're good.

261
00:15:33.729 --> 00:15:34.772
I don't need your busted up
watch sitting--

262
00:15:34.855 --> 00:15:36.482
Garcia!

263
00:15:36.565 --> 00:15:38.150
- Whoo!
- Sonny?

264
00:15:38.233 --> 00:15:40.152
[laughs]

265
00:15:42.655 --> 00:15:45.240
You spend my money already?
[laughs]

266
00:15:45.324 --> 00:15:46.909
No. I just-- I owe people.

267
00:15:46.992 --> 00:15:49.453
Oh. you owe me is who you owe.

268
00:15:49.536 --> 00:15:51.830
Hey. what happened
to you last night?

269
00:15:51.914 --> 00:15:55.042
Man. I had to sleep that off.

270
00:15:55.125 --> 00:15:56.377
What the hell was that shit?

271
00:15:56.460 --> 00:15:59.004
Tip of the iceberg.

272
00:15:59.088 --> 00:16:00.881
[inhales sharply]
Hey. listen. man.

273
00:16:00.965 --> 00:16:02.716
I manage a small business.

274
00:16:02.800 --> 00:16:06.053
and we're always
looking for smart guys.

275
00:16:06.136 --> 00:16:08.639
You look like a smart guy. Mike.

276
00:16:08.722 --> 00:16:11.684
What are you doing right now?

277
00:16:11.767 --> 00:16:13.143
You're looking at it.

278
00:16:13.227 --> 00:16:15.062
Let's go for a drive. unless you want

279
00:16:15.145 --> 00:16:18.065
to try your luck on Rodeo.
[chuckles]

280
00:16:18.148 --> 00:16:19.984
<i>♪ Remember ♪</i>

281
00:16:20.067 --> 00:16:20.943
[doorbell jingles]

282
00:16:25.197 --> 00:16:28.117
What rez you from? Hopi?

283
00:16:28.200 --> 00:16:29.994
Navajo.

284
00:16:30.077 --> 00:16:33.956
Right. the other one.

285
00:16:34.039 --> 00:16:36.041
Did you live there
till you were deployed?

286
00:16:36.125 --> 00:16:38.836
Nah. me and Mom
moved to Phoenix in high school.

287
00:16:38.919 --> 00:16:41.547
New kid in school.

288
00:16:41.630 --> 00:16:42.881
Bet you got all the girls.

289
00:16:42.965 --> 00:16:47.386
[chuckles] I did Okay.

290
00:16:47.469 --> 00:16:49.513
You got a girl now. right?

291
00:16:49.596 --> 00:16:51.223
That chick I saw you with at the party.

292
00:16:53.225 --> 00:16:54.435
Tawny?

293
00:16:54.518 --> 00:16:56.186
No. the other one--

294
00:16:56.270 --> 00:16:58.397
tall. serious looking.

295
00:17:00.941 --> 00:17:03.277
I don't know. man.
I was pretty messed up.

296
00:17:03.360 --> 00:17:05.320
[chuckles]

297
00:17:05.404 --> 00:17:09.158
Mike Garcia. free and easy.

298
00:17:09.241 --> 00:17:11.702
What can I say?

299
00:17:11.785 --> 00:17:13.746
You do like girls. though. right?

300
00:17:13.829 --> 00:17:15.914
Not judging.

301
00:17:15.998 --> 00:17:18.333
Just want to know what kind
of ride we're taking.

302
00:17:22.421 --> 00:17:24.048
[laughs]
I'm just playing with you. man!

303
00:17:24.131 --> 00:17:27.134
[laughing]

304
00:17:27.217 --> 00:17:29.595
Christ.
[laughs]

305
00:17:29.678 --> 00:17:32.514
- [chuckles]
- Stupid.

306
00:17:35.350 --> 00:17:38.145
Your mom still in Phoenix?

307
00:17:38.228 --> 00:17:40.731
No.

308
00:17:40.814 --> 00:17:45.235
No. she got pretty sick while I was gone.

309
00:17:45.319 --> 00:17:47.237
- Lung cancer.
- Oof.

310
00:17:47.321 --> 00:17:51.909
By the time IHS caught it. it was--

311
00:17:51.992 --> 00:17:53.994
she always wanted
to go back to the rez.

312
00:17:54.078 --> 00:17:55.954
though. before she died.

313
00:17:58.332 --> 00:18:01.710
She needed help. but I couldn't--

314
00:18:01.794 --> 00:18:03.587
you know. I wasn't there.

315
00:18:03.670 --> 00:18:05.631
You know?

316
00:18:05.714 --> 00:18:08.634
[somber music]

317
00:18:08.717 --> 00:18:09.802
<i>♪♪</i>

318
00:18:09.885 --> 00:18:11.970
You were drafted. man.

319
00:18:12.054 --> 00:18:13.931
Wasn't like you had a choice.

320
00:18:14.014 --> 00:18:16.892
[soft tense music]

321
00:18:16.975 --> 00:18:19.645
<i>♪♪</i>

322
00:18:19.728 --> 00:18:21.605
[clears throat softly]

323
00:18:36.203 --> 00:18:39.081
[moody guitar music]

324
00:18:39.164 --> 00:18:46.088
<i>♪♪</i>

325
00:18:52.886 --> 00:18:54.596
Agent Shaw's in the parking lot.

326
00:18:54.680 --> 00:18:56.598
Yeah. I see him.

327
00:18:56.682 --> 00:19:03.564
<i>♪♪</i>

328
00:19:13.448 --> 00:19:15.409
What do you want?

329
00:19:15.492 --> 00:19:17.286
If you're looking for Chee. he's not here.

330
00:19:17.369 --> 00:19:19.621
I was hoping to talk to you

331
00:19:19.705 --> 00:19:22.040
about the German and the green van.

332
00:19:22.124 --> 00:19:24.001
Do you have a minute?

333
00:19:24.084 --> 00:19:31.008
<i>♪♪</i>

334
00:19:42.853 --> 00:19:45.230
Welles and I just took over this case.

335
00:19:45.314 --> 00:19:47.566
Before that. it was
a guy named Ken Upchurch.

336
00:19:47.649 --> 00:19:50.611
He was a good agent. a friend.

337
00:19:50.694 --> 00:19:53.030
Found him in the garage yesterday.

338
00:19:53.113 --> 00:19:54.990
Car still running.

339
00:19:55.073 --> 00:19:58.994
The official position
is that he was a drunk

340
00:19:59.077 --> 00:20:00.662
and that his case was falling apart.

341
00:20:00.746 --> 00:20:03.790
and that's it.

342
00:20:03.874 --> 00:20:05.751
But you don't agree.

343
00:20:14.384 --> 00:20:17.304
I knew him pretty well.

344
00:20:17.387 --> 00:20:19.014
When you said
"green van" this morning.

345
00:20:19.097 --> 00:20:20.807
I remember one of Ken's neighbors

346
00:20:20.891 --> 00:20:22.392
saying he saw a green van parked

347
00:20:22.476 --> 00:20:25.520
on the street that night.

348
00:20:25.604 --> 00:20:28.357
Maybe it's the same green van.
Maybe it's not.

349
00:20:28.440 --> 00:20:30.734
Maybe it was dark
and the van was brown

350
00:20:30.817 --> 00:20:35.155
and this is all nothing.
but I owe it to Ken to try.

351
00:20:37.532 --> 00:20:40.410
And if you can link your van to mine.

352
00:20:40.494 --> 00:20:43.288
I can convince my SAC
to help look for your runaway.

353
00:20:43.372 --> 00:20:50.379
<i>♪♪</i>

354
00:20:50.504 --> 00:20:52.422
[traffic whooshing and groaning]

355
00:20:54.466 --> 00:20:57.386
[tense music]

356
00:20:57.469 --> 00:21:04.351
<i>♪♪</i>

357
00:21:08.063 --> 00:21:09.940
I'm looking for a teenage girl.

358
00:21:10.023 --> 00:21:13.026
- Billie Tsosie.
- I haven't seen her.

359
00:21:16.238 --> 00:21:20.409
Check with the Navajo police.
They were in here yesterday.

360
00:21:20.492 --> 00:21:27.416
<i>♪♪</i>

361
00:21:33.505 --> 00:21:36.341
[siren blaring distantly]

362
00:21:41.888 --> 00:21:43.473
[knocks] Tino!

363
00:21:43.557 --> 00:21:45.142
It's me!

364
00:21:48.645 --> 00:21:50.397
[gun clicks]

365
00:21:50.480 --> 00:21:52.733
[laughs]

366
00:21:52.816 --> 00:21:55.193
This one looks soft.

367
00:21:55.277 --> 00:21:59.364
Mikey? Nah. he's a killer.

368
00:21:59.448 --> 00:22:02.367
[dogs barking]

369
00:22:05.537 --> 00:22:07.372
[quietly] Jesus. man.

370
00:22:11.418 --> 00:22:13.295
What. no fries?

371
00:22:13.378 --> 00:22:15.464
Last time you said they were soggy.

372
00:22:15.547 --> 00:22:17.674
That don't mean I don't want 'em.

373
00:22:17.758 --> 00:22:19.968
Roman said you got something.

374
00:22:20.052 --> 00:22:22.387
Yeah. usual shit.

375
00:22:22.471 --> 00:22:26.183
Address is…

376
00:22:26.266 --> 00:22:29.144
[tense music]

377
00:22:29.227 --> 00:22:36.026
<i>♪♪</i>

378
00:22:38.653 --> 00:22:40.614
Jesus Christ. Really?

379
00:22:40.697 --> 00:22:41.907
He ain't gonna be happy seeing you.

380
00:22:44.201 --> 00:22:45.744
Nobody is.

381
00:22:47.037 --> 00:22:48.997
Come on.

382
00:22:51.208 --> 00:22:53.543
Next time. bring me
some goddamn fries.

383
00:22:56.171 --> 00:22:58.048
What are we doing here?

384
00:22:58.131 --> 00:22:59.758
I thought you said
you had a job for me.

385
00:22:59.841 --> 00:23:00.967
This is the interview.

386
00:23:01.760 --> 00:23:04.971
[in Diné] Hey. Hey boys.

387
00:23:07.599 --> 00:23:08.975
I know you.

388
00:23:10.352 --> 00:23:12.229
No. you must be mistaken.

389
00:23:12.312 --> 00:23:14.439
No. I know you.

390
00:23:17.984 --> 00:23:20.904
I remember your mother.
I remember what you did.

391
00:23:21.822 --> 00:23:25.826
I remember you calling out.
mother. mother. mother.

392
00:23:30.122 --> 00:23:31.581
[in English] Everything Okay?

393
00:23:31.665 --> 00:23:33.416
Yeah. she's crazy.

394
00:23:33.500 --> 00:23:34.835
All right. Come on. killer.

395
00:23:34.918 --> 00:23:37.546
You're burning my daylight.

396
00:23:37.629 --> 00:23:38.797
[door thuds]

397
00:23:38.880 --> 00:23:41.883
[engine rumbles]

398
00:23:41.967 --> 00:23:48.890
<i>♪♪</i>

399
00:23:53.728 --> 00:23:55.647
[tires squeal]

400
00:24:28.930 --> 00:24:31.808
[soft dramatic music]

401
00:24:31.892 --> 00:24:38.815
<i>♪♪</i>

402
00:25:04.925 --> 00:25:07.802
[breathing shakily]

403
00:25:14.726 --> 00:25:16.269
Hey.

404
00:25:21.942 --> 00:25:24.819
What's wrong?

405
00:25:24.903 --> 00:25:28.031
Who is this?

406
00:25:28.114 --> 00:25:33.161
Oh. that's Leroy's grandma.
or great grandma or something.

407
00:25:33.245 --> 00:25:34.746
Bentwoman.

408
00:25:34.829 --> 00:25:36.498
No. the younger one.

409
00:25:36.581 --> 00:25:41.294
<i>♪♪</i>

410
00:25:41.378 --> 00:25:43.088
His aunt.

411
00:25:43.171 --> 00:25:46.049
She takes care of the old lady.

412
00:25:46.132 --> 00:25:48.802
Why?

413
00:25:48.885 --> 00:25:50.971
I think it's my mom.

414
00:25:53.682 --> 00:25:54.766
[sniffles]

415
00:25:54.849 --> 00:25:57.852
[sobs quietly]

416
00:25:57.936 --> 00:25:59.854
Shicheii told me.

417
00:26:02.023 --> 00:26:05.068
He told me she died
right after I was born.

418
00:26:05.151 --> 00:26:08.113
He-- he told me she died.

419
00:26:08.196 --> 00:26:11.032
- Holy shit.
- [crying]

420
00:26:15.996 --> 00:26:18.498
They don't live that far.

421
00:26:18.581 --> 00:26:21.793
If you want. we could--

422
00:26:23.628 --> 00:26:25.714
Oh. my God.

423
00:26:25.797 --> 00:26:28.466
Leroy.

424
00:26:28.550 --> 00:26:30.302
I bet that's where Leroy is.

425
00:26:33.179 --> 00:26:34.723
[shakily] Let's go.

426
00:26:41.980 --> 00:26:44.232
[agent]<i> We know he ran</i>
<i>some errands that night--</i>

427
00:26:44.316 --> 00:26:46.026
<i>liquor store. dry cleaner.</i>

428
00:26:46.109 --> 00:26:47.444
Comes home with a bottle of scotch.

429
00:26:47.527 --> 00:26:49.112
writes this.

430
00:26:49.195 --> 00:26:51.114
Then he goes into the garage.
gets behind the wheel.

431
00:26:51.197 --> 00:26:53.074
starts the engine.

432
00:26:55.035 --> 00:26:56.786
No strange prints.

433
00:26:56.870 --> 00:26:59.539
Nothing missing except the dog.
but he could have run off.

434
00:26:59.622 --> 00:27:03.251
I don't know. maybe you guys
will see something we missed.

435
00:27:03.335 --> 00:27:05.295
What's the truth?

436
00:27:05.378 --> 00:27:08.423
[soft dramatic music]

437
00:27:08.506 --> 00:27:10.425
I wish I knew.

438
00:27:10.508 --> 00:27:17.432
<i>♪♪</i>

439
00:27:33.782 --> 00:27:35.325
You know his shoe size?

440
00:27:35.408 --> 00:27:37.160
Smaller than mine.

441
00:27:37.243 --> 00:27:39.120
Swapped shoes
once at the bowling alley.

442
00:27:39.204 --> 00:27:42.165
These are 11's.

443
00:27:42.248 --> 00:27:44.626
- Joe.
- Yeah?

444
00:27:44.709 --> 00:27:51.591
<i>♪♪</i>

445
00:27:56.388 --> 00:27:59.057
Upchurch ever visit
the Navajo reservation?

446
00:27:59.140 --> 00:28:00.642
Not that I know of.

447
00:28:00.725 --> 00:28:03.019
Well. this is from
the Trading Post on the rez.

448
00:28:03.103 --> 00:28:05.230
Any idea how
he could have gotten it?

449
00:28:05.313 --> 00:28:12.320
<i>♪♪</i>

450
00:28:12.445 --> 00:28:15.031
I'd like to take a look outside.

451
00:28:15.115 --> 00:28:20.036
<i>♪♪</i>

452
00:28:25.291 --> 00:28:28.128
Where was the van
parked the night Upchurch died?

453
00:28:28.211 --> 00:28:30.922
There.

454
00:28:39.681 --> 00:28:41.224
Where at?

455
00:28:41.307 --> 00:28:43.351
In front of the lamp post.

456
00:28:46.896 --> 00:28:49.733
[eerie electronic rattling]

457
00:28:58.158 --> 00:29:00.785
Has it rained?

458
00:29:00.869 --> 00:29:02.787
Yeah. Thursday.

459
00:29:26.936 --> 00:29:29.773
[eerie electronic thudding]

460
00:29:35.904 --> 00:29:42.827
<i>♪♪</i>

461
00:29:48.249 --> 00:29:49.793
It's an Army ration key.

462
00:29:49.876 --> 00:29:52.504
The little twist thing
they used to open 'em up.

463
00:29:52.587 --> 00:29:54.964
It's what the German eats
when she's on the job.

464
00:29:55.048 --> 00:29:57.383
Found one exactly like that
on the reservation

465
00:29:57.467 --> 00:29:59.803
where she was holed up
in the green van.

466
00:29:59.886 --> 00:30:02.764
[tense music]

467
00:30:02.847 --> 00:30:09.771
<i>♪♪</i>

468
00:30:14.317 --> 00:30:15.985
[grunts]

469
00:30:18.363 --> 00:30:20.824
That old woman got you messed up.

470
00:30:20.907 --> 00:30:22.659
I'm just hungover.

471
00:30:24.619 --> 00:30:27.163
I thought you said Leroy'd
be there last night.

472
00:30:27.247 --> 00:30:30.041
- Thought he was.
- Well. I didn't see him.

473
00:30:31.918 --> 00:30:35.380
Here's the thing.

474
00:30:35.463 --> 00:30:38.091
We live in a world that
old lady can't understand.

475
00:30:38.174 --> 00:30:40.134
Now. back in the day.
everything was black and white.

476
00:30:40.218 --> 00:30:44.597
Now the man
promises us good homes. jobs.

477
00:30:44.681 --> 00:30:47.267
makes us feel like
we're part of a team.

478
00:30:47.350 --> 00:30:50.019
And he comes. scoops us up.
and sends us to Vietnam

479
00:30:50.103 --> 00:30:53.356
to do his dirty work.
[exhales sharply]

480
00:30:53.439 --> 00:30:55.567
I swear. you can't trust
anyone over 30.

481
00:30:55.650 --> 00:30:59.863
[soft dramatic music]

482
00:30:59.946 --> 00:31:02.073
- How old are you?
- 42

483
00:31:02.156 --> 00:31:04.742
[laughter]

484
00:31:06.578 --> 00:31:09.831
Ah. I don't know.

485
00:31:09.914 --> 00:31:11.833
I go to Tino's a few times a week.

486
00:31:11.916 --> 00:31:13.626
I've seen that woman
hundreds of times.

487
00:31:13.710 --> 00:31:15.295
and she's never said one word to me.

488
00:31:17.255 --> 00:31:20.049
You don't speak Navajo.

489
00:31:20.133 --> 00:31:27.056
<i>♪♪</i>

490
00:31:27.140 --> 00:31:28.433
We're here.

491
00:31:28.516 --> 00:31:35.440
<i>♪♪</i>

492
00:31:43.156 --> 00:31:45.116
Probably won't need it.

493
00:31:45.199 --> 00:31:48.161
[clicks tongue]

494
00:31:48.244 --> 00:31:49.746
[door thuds]

495
00:31:56.502 --> 00:31:59.255
[funky music playing in background]

496
00:31:59.339 --> 00:32:05.678
<i>♪♪</i>

497
00:32:05.762 --> 00:32:08.264
[Isaac Hayes' "Do Your Thing" playing]

498
00:32:08.348 --> 00:32:11.309
<i>♪ If the music makes you move ♪</i>

499
00:32:11.392 --> 00:32:13.811
Hey. you wait right here.

500
00:32:13.895 --> 00:32:16.648
Sunshine. take care of killer for me.

501
00:32:16.731 --> 00:32:18.524
<i>♪♪</i>

502
00:32:18.608 --> 00:32:21.027
Uh. beer.

503
00:32:21.110 --> 00:32:24.030
<i>♪ If you feel like you want to make love ♪</i>

504
00:32:24.113 --> 00:32:25.031
<i>♪ Under the stars above ♪</i>

505
00:32:25.114 --> 00:32:26.950
Thank you.

506
00:32:27.033 --> 00:32:30.078
<i>♪ Love ♪</i>

507
00:32:30.161 --> 00:32:33.414
<i>♪ Love ♪</i>

508
00:32:33.498 --> 00:32:36.793
<i>♪ If it's something you want to say ♪</i>

509
00:32:36.876 --> 00:32:39.337
<i>♪ And talking is the only way ♪</i>

510
00:32:39.420 --> 00:32:42.840
<i>♪♪</i>

511
00:32:42.924 --> 00:32:47.345
Aw. Are you a horse?

512
00:32:47.428 --> 00:32:49.764
'Cause of the long face?

513
00:32:49.847 --> 00:32:51.265
I go on in 15. but I got time for a dance.

514
00:32:51.349 --> 00:32:53.059
Mm.

515
00:32:53.142 --> 00:32:54.686
I'll even give you
the early bird discount

516
00:32:54.769 --> 00:32:57.438
on account of your
exceptional sense of humor.

517
00:32:57.522 --> 00:32:59.440
I don't think my
girlfriend would like that.

518
00:32:59.524 --> 00:33:01.734
Oh. we could ask her. Is she here?

519
00:33:01.818 --> 00:33:03.903
- No.
- Then what's the matter?

520
00:33:03.987 --> 00:33:05.697
Me and my girl. we're in a fight.

521
00:33:05.780 --> 00:33:08.783
- Don't want to make it worse.
- Mm.

522
00:33:08.866 --> 00:33:10.952
- Girl troubles.
- Yeah.

523
00:33:11.035 --> 00:33:14.288
You know. I'm getting
my degree in psychotherapy.

524
00:33:14.372 --> 00:33:16.749
What's her name?

525
00:33:16.833 --> 00:33:18.418
Juliet.

526
00:33:18.501 --> 00:33:21.379
- That make you Romeo?
- No.

527
00:33:21.462 --> 00:33:23.548
[chuckles] You love her?

528
00:33:25.383 --> 00:33:27.218
Yeah. I do.

529
00:33:27.301 --> 00:33:30.221
She love you back?

530
00:33:30.304 --> 00:33:33.558
You know. I don't know.

531
00:33:33.641 --> 00:33:36.144
Her and a friend.
they lied about something big.

532
00:33:36.227 --> 00:33:39.605
- Were they fooling around?
- What? No.

533
00:33:39.689 --> 00:33:42.692
What then?

534
00:33:42.775 --> 00:33:47.155
It's-- don't you have
to get ready or something?

535
00:33:47.238 --> 00:33:50.199
Yeah. in a minute.

536
00:33:50.283 --> 00:33:52.827
I want to tell you something. buttercup.

537
00:33:52.910 --> 00:33:55.121
- Hm.
- There's two kinds of lies.

538
00:33:55.204 --> 00:33:56.706
The kind you tell to hurt people

539
00:33:56.789 --> 00:33:59.500
and the kind you tell to protect 'em.

540
00:33:59.584 --> 00:34:01.544
Which one your girl tell?

541
00:34:01.627 --> 00:34:03.254
[screams]

542
00:34:03.337 --> 00:34:04.922
[door clicks]

543
00:34:05.006 --> 00:34:07.425
[tense music]

544
00:34:07.508 --> 00:34:09.218
What's going on? You Okay?

545
00:34:09.302 --> 00:34:12.221
We got to go. Now.

546
00:34:12.305 --> 00:34:13.973
- Gun!
- Ow!

547
00:34:14.057 --> 00:34:15.183
[gunshot]

548
00:34:15.266 --> 00:34:16.601
Go.

549
00:34:16.684 --> 00:34:18.061
- [laughs]
- Are you hit?

550
00:34:18.144 --> 00:34:19.562
Go. go. go. go!
Drive! Drive! Drive! Drive!

551
00:34:19.645 --> 00:34:22.565
[suspenseful music]

552
00:34:22.648 --> 00:34:23.900
[engine rumbles]

553
00:34:23.983 --> 00:34:25.943
Go. go. go. go. go. go. go. go!

554
00:34:26.027 --> 00:34:28.780
<i>♪♪</i>

555
00:34:28.863 --> 00:34:30.364
Oh. my God! Oh. my God!

556
00:34:30.448 --> 00:34:31.324
[tires squeal]

557
00:34:31.407 --> 00:34:33.743
[gunshot]

558
00:34:33.826 --> 00:34:35.703
[laughs]

559
00:34:35.787 --> 00:34:37.622
[gunshot]

560
00:34:37.705 --> 00:34:40.625
[cheering]

561
00:34:45.338 --> 00:34:48.508
- God damn that hurt!
- [Sonny groans]

562
00:34:48.591 --> 00:34:51.511
And I just got this couch. Get a towel.

563
00:34:51.594 --> 00:34:54.138
Down the hallway. bathroom.

564
00:34:54.222 --> 00:34:57.100
[suspenseful music]

565
00:34:57.183 --> 00:35:04.107
<i>♪♪</i>

566
00:35:16.327 --> 00:35:18.204
Hurry up!

567
00:35:32.009 --> 00:35:34.303
- [inhales sharply]
- Oh. God.

568
00:35:34.387 --> 00:35:35.847
You need a doctor. man.

569
00:35:35.930 --> 00:35:37.640
I don't need a doctor
wondering how I got shot.

570
00:35:37.723 --> 00:35:40.393
- Just patch it up.
- You need stitches.

571
00:35:40.476 --> 00:35:42.311
Go get some stitches.

572
00:35:42.395 --> 00:35:44.438
Hallway. closet!

573
00:35:44.522 --> 00:35:47.400
[breathing raggedly]

574
00:35:50.778 --> 00:35:52.530
Agh! Damn it!

575
00:35:52.613 --> 00:35:54.574
And bring me a drink!

576
00:35:54.657 --> 00:35:55.616
Here.

577
00:35:55.700 --> 00:36:02.331
<i>♪♪</i>

578
00:36:02.415 --> 00:36:04.333
[Sonny groans]

579
00:36:04.417 --> 00:36:07.378
[panting]

580
00:36:08.546 --> 00:36:10.131
[grunts]

581
00:36:12.550 --> 00:36:14.969
- [hyperventilates]
- All right. you ready?

582
00:36:15.052 --> 00:36:16.929
Uh-huh.

583
00:36:20.349 --> 00:36:23.311
[groans]

584
00:36:23.394 --> 00:36:30.401
<i>♪♪</i>

585
00:36:30.526 --> 00:36:32.486
It's a pretty good stitch for a war dog.

586
00:36:32.570 --> 00:36:34.697
Drink up. You got a dozen more.

587
00:36:34.780 --> 00:36:36.157
[hisses]

588
00:36:36.240 --> 00:36:41.954
<i>♪♪</i>

589
00:36:42.038 --> 00:36:44.957
[screams]

590
00:36:50.755 --> 00:36:54.634
I had this girlfriend

591
00:36:54.717 --> 00:36:57.011
when I first got down here.

592
00:36:59.972 --> 00:37:01.849
She was real foxy.

593
00:37:03.976 --> 00:37:09.690
Real tall Navajo.

594
00:37:11.567 --> 00:37:13.027
She ran away
from home but would

595
00:37:13.110 --> 00:37:15.947
call her mom almost every day.

596
00:37:19.325 --> 00:37:22.787
Must have spent a fortune
in long-distance.

597
00:37:25.748 --> 00:37:27.166
<i>Shimá!</i>

598
00:37:29.919 --> 00:37:33.381
I remember that word.

599
00:37:35.800 --> 00:37:37.385
<i>Shimá!</i>

600
00:37:39.178 --> 00:37:40.763
<i>Shimá.</i>

601
00:37:42.640 --> 00:37:44.600
<i>Shimá.</i>

602
00:37:49.188 --> 00:37:51.065
[bottle clinks]

603
00:37:53.109 --> 00:37:56.862
[exhales deeply] Sonny.

604
00:38:07.290 --> 00:38:08.457
Sonny?

605
00:38:23.889 --> 00:38:25.516
[door clicks]

606
00:38:25.599 --> 00:38:28.519
[dramatic music]

607
00:38:28.602 --> 00:38:30.813
<i>♪♪</i>

608
00:38:30.896 --> 00:38:32.148
Sonny?

609
00:38:33.065 --> 00:38:39.989
<i>♪♪</i>

610
00:38:41.198 --> 00:38:43.617
[car horn honks]

611
00:38:43.701 --> 00:38:50.624
<i>♪♪</i>

612
00:40:18.129 --> 00:40:20.423
[quietly] Hi. yeah. I want to leave

613
00:40:20.506 --> 00:40:23.217
a message for Joe Leaphorn.
He's in room 21.

614
00:40:23.300 --> 00:40:25.970
Tell him to meet Chee at

615
00:40:26.053 --> 00:40:30.975
2113 Normandie.

616
00:40:31.058 --> 00:40:34.812
apartment 527.

617
00:40:34.895 --> 00:40:39.358
Yeah. tell him I found Leroy.

618
00:41:17.688 --> 00:41:20.065
[knocks]

619
00:41:20.149 --> 00:41:22.776
Leroy.

620
00:41:26.530 --> 00:41:29.450
[knocks]

621
00:41:29.533 --> 00:41:32.495
Billie. you in there?

622
00:41:32.578 --> 00:41:35.456
[tense music]

623
00:41:35.539 --> 00:41:42.463
<i>♪♪</i>

624
00:42:09.198 --> 00:42:11.158
[sniffs]

625
00:42:11.242 --> 00:42:18.123
<i>♪♪</i>

626
00:42:59.957 --> 00:43:03.085
[gasps sharply]

627
00:43:03.168 --> 00:43:05.129
[sighs]

628
00:43:09.091 --> 00:43:11.969
[breathing raggedly]

629
00:43:14.847 --> 00:43:16.098
[grunts]

630
00:43:20.352 --> 00:43:22.730
[muffled wheezing from bathroom]

631
00:43:25.149 --> 00:43:26.817
[groans]

632
00:43:26.900 --> 00:43:29.737
[continues wheezing from bathroom]

633
00:43:38.078 --> 00:43:45.002
<i>♪♪</i>

634
00:44:00.809 --> 00:44:03.479
[wheezing]

635
00:44:03.562 --> 00:44:05.481
[door creaks]

636
00:44:05.564 --> 00:44:08.484
[wheezing]

637
00:44:08.567 --> 00:44:15.491
<i>♪♪</i>

638
00:44:42.726 --> 00:44:43.852
[grunts]

639
00:44:43.936 --> 00:44:46.647
[gun clicks]

640
00:44:46.730 --> 00:44:49.525
Who the fuck are you?

641
00:44:49.608 --> 00:44:51.902
[intense music]

642
00:44:56.615 --> 00:44:59.535
[soft tense music]

643
00:44:59.618 --> 00:45:06.542
<i>♪♪</i>
